item.description:
A politician is someone who is currently running for or holding a state or federal government seat.

## Properties

A politician has the following properties.

- ID: A long, database id.
- Name: The name of the politician.
- Elected: A boolean telling whether this politician is currently holding elected office or not.
- Party: One letter denoting Democrat, Republican, Libertarian, or Independent.
- Terms: 
    - Current: Which term is this incumbent serving.
    - Total: Total terms this incumbent has served in government.
- Offices:
    - Current: An abbreviated string denoting which seat of office this incumbent is holding.
    - Past: An array of abbreviated strings denoting which seats this politician has held in the past.
    - Running For: An abbreviate string denoting which seat of office this challenger is running for.
- District:
    - Name: The name of this district, State-Number (e.g. TX-1).
    - ID: The ID of the district object in our database.
- Image: A URL of the candidate's beautiful, or ugly, face.
- Socials: 
    - Facebook: The candidate's Facebook.
    - Twitter: The candidate's Twitter.
    - Instagram: The candidate's Instagram.
    - YouTube: The candidate's YouTube.
- Website: The candidate's campaign website. This is not the same thing as the candidate's office website if the candidate is currently holding office.
- Elections:
    - Upcoming: 
        - ID: The ID of the upcoming election this candidate is participating in.
    - Past: Array of IDs.
        - ID: IDs of the past election this candidate has run in.
- Fundraising: 
    - Raised: The amount of money the candidate has raised for the current election cycle.
    - Spent: The amount of money the candidate has spent for the current election cycle.
    - Remaining Cash: The amount of money the candidate can still use for the current election cycle.
    - Contributors: Array of objects.
        - Type: Whether the category is small donations (donations under $250), large donations (donations over $250), PAC donations, self financed money, or another source.
        - Amount: The amount of money of the above type.

item.name: Districts
Details about districts based on passed queries.

item.description:
A district is the geographic area that a politician represents and which the seat is located in. The district's location and boundaries are decided by the Texas Legislature.

## Properties

- ID: The long database ID of this district object.
- Name: The name of this district, formatted "State-Number" (e.g. TX-1).
- Type: Whether this is a state house, state senate, US House, US Senate district, or other.
- Party: The one letter abbreviation for the party that currently controls this district.
- Counties: An array of counties this district partially or fully covers.
- Number: The number of this district.
- Map: A link to a map showing the district boundaries.
- Elections:
    - Current: 
        - ID: The ID to the current election in our database.
    - Past: An array of IDs of past elections.
        - ID: The ID of the past election in our database.
- Elected Officials: Array of politicians who hold office in this district.
    - Name: Name of this politician.
    - ID: ID of this politician in our database.
- Demographics:
    - Total Population: The total population of residents living in this district.
    - Age: 
        - 0: Population from 0-5.
        - 5: Population from 5-17.
        - 18: Population from 18-64
        - 65: Population above 65.
    - Race:
        - White: White population in this district.
        - Black: African American and Black population in this district.
        - Indigenous: Native American and Alaskan Native population in this district.
        - Asian: Asian American population in this district.
        - Pacific Islander: Native Hawaiian, American Samoan, and other Pacific Islander population in this district.
    - Ethnicity:
        - Hispanic: Hispanic population in this district.
        - Non Hispanic: Non-hispanic population in this district.
    - Educational Attainment:
        - Enrollment: Object of population under 25 possibly still attending school.
            - Preschool: Population in pre-school.
            - Primary: Population in elementary, middle, and high school.
            - University: Population enrolled in an undergraduate or graduate program.
        - Attainment: Object of population at and over 25 in the district.
            - High School: Population who only have a high school degree, GED, or lower.
            - Some College: Population who have some college experience or have obtained an associates but not bachelors or equivalent.
            - Bachelors: Population who have obtained a bachelors degree or higher.
    - Income
        - 0: Population with an income between $0 and $9,999.
        - 10 000: Population with an income between $10,000 and $24,999.
        - 25 000: Population with an income between $25,000 and $49,999.
        - 50 000: Population with an income between $50,000 and $99,999.
        - 100 000: Population with an income between $100,000 and $199,999.
        - 200 000: Population with an income at and over $200,000.

Details about an election

item.description:
An election is the competition between politicians running for a given office within a district.

## Properties

- ID: Long database ID of this election object.
- Type: String denoting whether this election is a primary, runoff, special, or general election.
- Dates: 
    - Early Start: The early voting start date.
    - Early End: The early voting end date.
    - Election Day: The regular voting date.
- Candidates: Array of all candidates participating in this election.
    - Name: The name of the current candidate.
    - Party: The one letter abbreviation of the candidate's party.
    - ID: The ID of this current candidate.
- District: 
    - Name: The name of the district this election is being held in.
    - ID: The long ID of the corresponding district object in our database.
- Office: The abbreviated name of the seat type the election is for.
- Results: 
    - Winner: 
        - Name: The name of the winning politician.
        - Party: The one letter abbreviation of the winner's party.
        - ID: The winner's long ID to the corresponding politician in our database.
    - Vote Counts: An array of short candidate objects that contains vote tallies they got.
        - Name: The name of the current candidate.
        - Party: The one letter abbreviation of the candidate's party.
        - ID: The long ID of the coresponding politician object in our database.
        - Vote Total: The total amount of votes this candidate got.
        - Vote Percentage: The percentage share of votes the candidate got out of all participants.
    - Total Voters: The total amount of voters who turned out to this election.
